## Executive Overview

The NEO AIRFLOW NODE represents the third and final component of the PI220 Tri-Node Architecture.

Where:

* NEO HYDRAULIC MATRIX governs structural stability
* NEO THERMAL NODE governs thermal stability

the NEO AIRFLOW NODE governs aerodynamic stability.

Its purpose is to create a continuously adaptive atmospheric interaction system capable of monitoring, predicting, and optimizing airflow throughout an aerospace platform.

Unlike conventional aircraft, where airflow is primarily managed through fixed aerodynamic surfaces, the NEO AIRFLOW NODE introduces a distributed airflow intelligence model.

The objective is simple:

> Airflow should not be reacted to.

> Airflow should be understood, predicted, and guided.

The NEO AIRFLOW NODE becomes the direct technological predecessor to:

* AFAT-X10
* AFAT-X10 V2
* AFAT-X10 V2 Full Deployment Model
* Boeing 220-G Global

